Kai Henningsen wrote:
> * typically uses one- or two-character variable names
At ETH, we jokingly called this WNF ("Wirth's Normal Form". Well,
actually "Wirthsche Normalform"): shortening any identifier name
would make it conflict with another one.
Isn't it funny how irrelevant those Pascal-family languages
become, once you grok C ? :-)
